  "name": "Whip Maneuver",
  "type": "technique",
  "img": "icons/weapons/misc/whip-red-yellow.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": "<p><strong>Style Passive: </strong>You deal +1 damage against creatures that are farther than 1 Space from you.</p>\n<p><strong>Requires: </strong>Attack Check</p>\n<p><strong>Maneuver: (1 AP)</strong> You deal +1 damage, and the target makes a <strong>Physical Save </strong>against being tethered by your Whip. You can&nbsp;release the target at any time.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Tethered Creatures:</strong> While you are wielding the Whip and&nbsp;the target is tethered by it, you can&rsquo;t use the Whip to make&nbsp;<strong>Attack Checks</strong>.&nbsp;<br>Additionally, if the target is the same size as you or smaller it can&rsquo;t move farther than the Whip&rsquo;s range from you.</li>\n<li><strong>Pull Creature: &nbsp;</strong>You can spend <strong>1 AP </strong>to make a Contested Athletics Check against the target. <br><strong>Contest Success: </strong>The&nbsp;target is pulled 1 Space in a direction of your choice within&nbsp;your Whip&rsquo;s range and falls <strong>Prone</strong>.</li>\n<li><strong>Escape Tether: </strong>The creature can spend <strong>1 AP </strong>to make a <strong>Contested Martial Check </strong>against you. <br><strong>Success:</strong> The target&nbsp;frees itself from your Whip.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>System Tip: </strong>You can add Weapon Maneuvers as Weapon Enhacements for easier use. Just press \"Add Martial Maneuvers For Weapon\" on <strong>Enhancements </strong>tab on <strong>Item </strong>sheet.</em></p>",
